 membrane filtration chromatography, vacuum concentration and spray drying.\r\n\r\nFunctions:\r\nAnti-oxidation\r\nRemoval of free radicals\r\nRegulation of blood lipids and cholesterols\r\nAnti-inflammation and strengthen immune functions\r\nContain anti-aging and anti-wrinkle factors\r\n\r\nApplications:\r\n-As dietary supplements: intake as capsules.\r\n-As ingredient: in other Nutritional products such as milk powder, Nutritional beverage (Bamboo Beer, Bamboo Water), etc.\r\n-Adding to regular foods to increase its nutrition values such as rice/noodle.\r\n-As cosmetic ingredient used in skin-care products.','Bamboo Leaves ','','inherit','closed','closed','','654-revision-v1','','','2013-09-16 06:19:52','2013-09-16 06:19:52','',654,'http://ansbotanics.com/?p=1427',0,'revision','',0),(1428,2,'2013-09-16 06:22:21','2013-09-16 06:22:21','Product Name: Basil Powder Extract\nLatin Name: Ocimum Sanctum\nChinese Name:Luo Le\nSpecification: Alkaloids 0.2%,0.3% HPLC\n\nDescription:\nThis annual herb is from the Lamiaceae family. The name Basil is from the Greek word \"Basileus\" which means \"King\". Basil is also known as St. Joseph wort. As an annual plant with branchy roots, Basil can grow up to three feet high with flowers that vary widely in color. Basil has a rich and fanciful history. It had been \'Herb royale\' to the French, a sign of love to Italians, and a sacred herb in India. The first century A.D. Roman naturalist Pliny reported that basil relieves flatulence, which had been subsequently proven true. In the Far East, the herb had been used as a cough medicine, and in Africa, it has been used to expel worms. American colonists considered Basil the essential ingredient in a snuff used to ease headaches.\n\nFunctions:\nA poultice of Basil leaves can help draw out insect, bee wasp, or snake venom. It can help cure acne, heal abrasions, cuts and gives a persons hair a high shine after it is used as a rinse. Popularly know as basil, Tulsi is an extremely aromatic and stimulating herb. It has many antibacterial, anti-stress, anti-fungal, and antibiotic properties. The aroma of tulsi is conducive to meditation. It is used in many skin treatments, and is particularly helpful in smoothening and softening the skin. Leaves and seeds are used to treat skin problems; roots are used for fever, bee stings, and insect bites. Other uses include treating nausea, motion sickness, gastric and liver disorders, diarrhea, and vomiting. The functions described above are believed to be due to the alkaloids in Basil.\nWith abundant vitamins A, D, and B2, as well as the minerals calcium, iron, magnesium and phosphorus, Basil is also used for culinary taste, as well as for medicine.','Basil Extract ','','inherit','closed','closed','','657-autosave-v1','','','2013-09-16 06:22:21','2013-09-16 06:22:21','',657,'http://ansbotanics.com/?p=1428',0,'revision','',0),(1429,2,'2013-09-16 06:25:49','2013-09-16 06:25:49','','Basil Extract','','inherit','closed','closed','','basil-extract','','','2013-09-16 06:25:49','2013-09-16 06:25:49','',657,'http://ansbotanics.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Basil-Extract.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1430,2,'2013-09-16 06:26:25','2013-09-16 06:26:25','Product Name: Basil Powder Extract\r\nLatin Name: Ocimum Sanctum\r\nChinese Name:Luo Le\r\nSpecification: Alkaloids 0.2%,0.3% HPLC\r\n\r\nDescription:\r\nThis annual herb is from the Lamiaceae family. The name Basil is from the Greek word \"Basileus\" which means \"King\". Basil is also known as St. Joseph wort. As an annual plant with branchy roots, Basil can grow up to three feet high with flowers that vary widely in color. Basil has a rich and fanciful history. It had been \'Herb royale\' to the French, a sign of love to Italians, and a sacred herb in India. The first century A.D. Roman naturalist Pliny reported that basil relieves flatulence, which had been subsequently proven true. In the Far East, the herb had been used as a cough medicine, and in Africa, it has been used to expel worms. American colonists considered Basil the essential ingredient in a snuff used to ease headaches.\r\n\r\nFunctions:\r\nA poultice of Basil leaves can help draw out insect, bee wasp, or snake venom. It can help cure acne, heal abrasions, cuts and gives a persons hair a high shine after it is used as a rinse. Popularly know as basil, Tulsi is an extremely aromatic and stimulating herb. It has many antibacterial, anti-stress, anti-fungal, and antibiotic properties. The aroma of tulsi is conducive to meditation. It is used in many skin treatments, and is particularly helpful in smoothening and softening the skin. Leaves and seeds are used to treat skin problems; roots are used for fever, bee stings, and insect bites. Other uses include treating nausea, motion sickness, gastric and liver disorders, diarrhea, and vomiting. The functions described above are believed to be due to the alkaloids in Basil.\r\nWith abundant vitamins A, D, and B2, as well as the minerals calcium, iron, magnesium and phosphorus, Basil is also used for culinary taste, as well as for medicine.','Basil Extract ','','inherit','closed','closed','','657-revision-v1','','','2013-09-16 06:26:25','2013-09-16 06:26:25','',657,'http://ansbotanics.com/?p=1430',0,'revision','',0),(1431,2,'2013-09-16 06:27:51','2013-09-16 06:27:51','','Bayberry Bark Extract Myricetin','','inherit','closed','closed','','bayberry-bark-extract-myricetin-2','','','2013-09-16 06:27:51','2013-09-16 06:27:51','',660,'http://ansbotanics.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Bayberry-Bark-Extract-Myricetin1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1432,2,'2013-09-16 06:28:05','2013-09-16 06:28:05','Product Name: Bayberry Bark Dry Extract (Myricetin)\r\nFormula: C15H10O8\r\nCAS No. 529-44-2\r\nMW: 318.2\r\n\r\nDescription:\r\nMyricetin is a flavonoid that is commonly found in natural food sources such as berries, vegetables, teas, wine and herbs.\r\nMyricetin is considered to be an antioxidant, which means that it is capable of eliminating cancer causing free radicals within the body.\r\nIt is usually taken from the bark, leaves, and roots of the plant known as myrica cerifera.Myricetin is commonly marketed as an ingredient in products to help consumers stop smoking. It is believed that Myricetin blocks certain enzymes within the body. Myricetin is also considered to be an antioxidant, ridding the body of cancer causing free radicals.\r\n\r\nFunctionts:\r\nTreatment for diarrhea\r\nTreatment for Dysentery\r\nTreatment for fevers\r\nLower high cholesterol levels\r\nReduce the risk of prostate cancer in men','Bayberry Bark Extract ','','inherit','closed','closed','','660-revision-v1','','','2013-09-16 06:28:05','2013-09-16 06:28:05','',660,'http://ansbotanics.com/?p=1432',0,'revision','',0),(1433,2,'2013-09-16 06:45:06','2013-09-16 06:45:06','','Bearberry Extract','','inherit','closed','closed','','bearberry-extract','','','2013-09-16 06:45:06','2013-09-16 06:45:06','',663,'http://ansbotanics.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Bearberry-Extract.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1434,2,'2013-09-16 06:49:59','2013-09-16 06:49:59','','bitter melon','','inherit','closed','closed','','bitter-melon','','','2013-09-16 06:49:59','2013-09-16 06:49:59','',669,'http://ansbotanics.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/bitter-melon.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1435,2,'2013-09-16 06:50:13','2013-09-16 06:50:13','Product Name: Bitter Melon Powder Extract\r\nLatin Name: Momordica charantia\r\nChinese Name: Ku gua\r\nSpecification: 10:1\r\n\r\nDescription:\r\nThe plant Momordica charantia belongs to the family cucuritaceae and is commonly known as bitter melon. Bitter melon grows in tropical and subtropic areas, including parts of East Africa, Asia, the Caribbean, and South America, where it is used as a food as well as a medicine. It produces beautiful flowers and prickly fruit .The fruit of this plant lives up to its nameit tastes bitter. Although the seeds, leaves, and vines of bitter melon have all been used, the fruit is the safest and most prevalent part of the plant used medicinally. The juice of the leaves and fruit or seeds is used as an anthelmintic. In Brazil, the dose for anthelmintic use is two or three seeds. The immature fruit of M.charantia tastes bitter due to the cucurbitacius. Cucurbitacius is comprised of a group of triterpenes including momordicosides, A-E, K, L, and momardicius I, II and III. The roots and fruit are used as an abortifacient.\r\n\r\nIn traditional herbal medicine, bitter melon is thought to stimulate digestive function and improve appetite. This has yet to be tested in human studies.Being a relatively common food item, bitter melon was traditionally used for an array of conditions by people in tropical regions. Numerous infections, cancer, and diabetes are among the most common conditions it was purported to improve.1 Unripe fruit, seeds and aerial parts ofMomordica charantiaLinn. have been used in various parts of the world to treat diabetes. The leaves and fruit have both been used to make teas and beer or to season soups in the Western world. Nowadays Bitter Melon capsules and tinctures are widely available in the Western world where in herbal medicine they are being used for diabetes, HIV and other viruses, colds and flu and psoriasis.\r\n\r\nFunctions:\r\nAnti-diabetic Activity\r\nAnti-virus activity and etc.','Bitter Melon Extract ','','inherit','closed','closed','','669-revision-v1','','','2013-09-16 06:50:13','2013-09-16 06:50:13','',669,'http://ansbotanics.com/?p=1435',0,'revision','',0),(1436,2,'2013-09-16 06:55:06','2013-09-16 06:55:06','','Black Cohosh Extract','','inherit','closed','closed','','black-cohosh-extract','','','2013-09-16 06:55:06','2013-09-16 06:55:06','',672,'http://ansbotanics.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Black-Cohosh-Extract.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1437,2,'2013-09-16 06:57:27','2013-09-16 06:57:27','','Black Currant Anthocyandins','','inherit','closed','closed','','black-currant-anthocyandins-2','','','2013-09-16 06:57:27','2013-09-16 06:57:27','',675,'http://ansbotanics.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Black-Currant-Anthocyandins1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1438,2,'2013-09-16 06:57:43','2013-09-16 06:57:43','Product Name: Black Currant Powder Extract\r\nSpecification: Anthocyanidins 25% UV\r\n\r\nDescription:\r\nBlack currant, like Bilberry, is rich in Anthocyanidins.The roles of Anthocyanidins pigments as medicinal agents have been well-accepted dogma in folk medicine throughout the world, and, in fact, these pigments are linked to an amazingly broad-based range of health benefits.\r\n\r\nFunctions:\r\nEnhance night vision or overall vision\r\nReduce cancer cell proliferation and to inhibit tumor formation\r\nPrevent obesity and diabetes\r\nPrevent age-related declines in neural function\r\nEnhance memory','Black Currant Extract','','inherit','closed','closed','','675-revision-v1','','','2013-09-16 06:57:43','2013-09-16 06:57:43','',675,'http://ansbotanics.com/?p=1438',0,'revision','',0),(1439,2,'2013-09-16 07:06:10','2013-09-16 07:06:10','','Cassia Nomame Extract','','inherit','closed','closed','','cassia-nomame-extract','','','2013-09-16 07:06:10','2013-09-16 07:06:10','',681,'http://ansbotanics.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Cassia-Nomame-Extract.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1440,2,'2013-09-16 07:08:05','2013-09-16 07:08:05','','Chinese Fox-Glove Root Extract','','inherit','closed','closed','','chinese-fox-glove-root-extract-2','','','2013-09-16 07:08:05','2013-09-16 07:08:05','',684,'http://ansbotanics.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Chinese-Fox-Glove-Root-Extract1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1441,2,'2013-09-16 07:12:14','2013-09-16 07:12:14','','Citrus Aurantium','','inherit','closed','closed','','citrus-aurantium','','','2013-09-16 07:12:14','2013-09-16 07:12:14','',687,'http://ansbotanics.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Citrus-Aurantium.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1442,2,'2013-09-16 07:12:27','2013-09-16 07:12:27','Product Name: Citrus Aurantium Powder Extract\r\nLatin Name: Citrus Aurantium\r\nSpecification: Synephrine 4%-30%\r\n\r\nDescription:\r\nCitrus aurantium L, belonging to the family Rutaceae, is widely distributed in China. Zhishi, the Chinese traditional name for Citrus aurantium, has long been a folk medicine in traditional Chinese medicine (TCM) to improve indigestion and help stimulate the Qi (energy force).It also has been a folk remedy in Italy since the 16th century for fevers like malaria and as an antiseptic. Recent studies have confirmed that Zhishi, replacing Ma Huang, can be used for treatment of obesity without the negative cardiovascular side effects.\r\n\r\nFunctions:\r\nWeight Loss\r\nMild Exhilarant\r\nDigestive Tract Discomfort\r\nAnti-Microbial Activities\r\n\r\nSynepherine is the main active compound found in the fruit of Citrus aurantium, which is effective in providing the energy boost (caloric expenditure), aiding the expulsion of wind, warming the stomach, improving the appetite, and increasing metabolic rate. Citrus aurantium is theorized to stimulate fat metabolism without the negative cardiovascular side effects experienced by some people using Ma Huang. It is also a mild aromatic expectorant, a nervine and a laxation for constipation.','Citrus Aurantium ','','inherit','closed','closed','','687-revision-v1','','','2013-09-16 07:12:27','2013-09-16 07:12:27','',687,'http://ansbotanics.com/?p=1442',0,'revision','',0),(1443,2,'2013-09-16 07:15:02','2013-09-16 07:15:02','','Dandelion Extract Taraxacum mongolicum','','inherit','closed','closed','','dandelion-extract-taraxacum-mongolicum-2','','','2013-09-16 07:15:02','2013-09-16 07:15:02','',690,'http://ansbotanics.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/08/Dandelion-Extract-Taraxacum-mongolicum1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(1444,2,'2013-09-16 07:17:43','2013-09-16 07:17:43','','Echinacea Extract Plolyphenols','','inherit','closed','closed','','echinacea-extract-plolyphenols-2','','','20